(69, 'news-amp-events', 'evnfinance-news', 'evnfinance-and-the-environmental-protection-fund-of-vietnam-have-signed-cooperation-agreements', 'EVNFinance and the Environmental Protection Fund of Vietnam have signed cooperation agreements', 'admin', '1293763243', 'admin', '1293763243', 'english', 0, 2, '<p>November 18, 2010 in Hanoi, EVN Finance Joint Stock Company (EVNFinance) and the Environmental Protection Fund of Vietnam (VEPF) signed a comprehensive cooperation agreement.</p>', '<p><img width="450" height="300" alt="" src="/data/upload/image/Meco.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p>November 18, 2010 in Hanoi, EVN Finance Joint Stock Company (EVNFinance) and the Environmental Protection Fund of Vietnam (VEPF) signed a comprehensive cooperation agreement.</p>\r\n<p>Accordingly, the two organizations agreed to cooperate in the provision and use of financial services, information sharing, execution of activities to support professional development, to promote the brand, etc...</p>\r\n<p>Environmental Protection Fund of Vietnam is a state financial institution, has the function of receiving funds from the state budget, sponsor sources, contributions, fiduciary money of domestic and international organizations and individuals to finance for environmental protection activities over the country.</p>\r\n<p>Being approved by EVN Board of Directors as a focal institution to develop CDM projects (the Clean Development Mechanism projects) of the Vietnam Electricity Corporation, EVNFinance provides CDM consulting services. Currently, EVNFinance acts as the portfolio manager with more than 30 CDM projects in power sector.</p>\r\n<p>Under the above agreement contents, the two parties will carry out co-financing, lending for feasible, environmental protection projects under the priority areas, meeting the requirements upon the selected criteria. EVNFinance will provide financial management hub for a number of environmental protection programs and projects that VEPF, EVNFinance and/or any third party involved credit arrangements.</p>\r\n<p>This comprehensive cooperation Agreement between VEPF and EVNFinance is remarkable event for both parties in efforts developing a green environment, paving the way for a sustainable development./.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '12_2010_69.jpg', '', 1, 'unhide'),
(70, 'news-amp-events', 'evnfinance-news', 'evnfinance-is-assigned-to-be-a-re-lending-institution-with-incentive-interest-rate-for-vinh-tan-2-thermal-power-plant-project', 'EVNFinance is assigned to be a re-lending institution with incentive interest rate for Vinh Tan 2 Thermal Power Plant Project', 'admin', '1293763597', 'ducnt', '1471944224', 'english', 0, 2, '<p>On December 17th, Vietnam Deputy Finance Minister Tran Xuan Ha and Vice Chairman of Export Bank of China - Su Zhong signed the specific loan agreement for thermal power plant project in Vinh Tan 2 up to $ 300 million.</p>', '<p><img width=\\"450\\" height=\\"318\\" src=\\"/data/upload/image/Vinh%20Tan%202.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" /></p>\r\n<p>On December 17th, Vietnam Deputy Finance Minister Tran Xuan Ha and Vice Chairman of Export Bank of China - Su Zhong signed the specific loan agreement for thermal power plant project in Vinh Tan 2 up to $ 300 million.</p>\r\n<p>This Agreement concretizes the framework agreement on the credit for incentive buyer signed on September 07th, 2009 between the Ministry of Finance, Vietnam and the Export-Import Bank of China. The credit will fund the Electricity of Vietnam (EVN) to build the Vinh Tan 2 Thermal Power Plant in Binh Thuan province.</p>\r\n<p>The Plant has a total installed capacity of 1244 MW with two units, the power output of annual production is about 7.2 billion kWh. According to deployment progress, the first units of the Vinh Tan 2 Thermal Power Plant will officially operate in December, 2013 and the latter is in the month June, 2014.</p>\r\n<p>EVN Finance Joint Stock Company (EVNFinance) has been approved by Vietnamese Government to carry out the role of re-financing institution for the project. After more than two operating years, EVNFinance has gradually defined effective target to be the focal unit of capital management and arrangement for the Electricity of Vietnam and other members, step by step asserted its position on domestic financial market./.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '12_2010_70.jpg', '', 1, ''),
