(54, 'news-amp-events', 'evnfinance-news', 'evn-finance-celebrating-1st-anniversary', 'EVN Finance Celebrating 1st Anniversary', 'admin', '1293519774', 'admin', '1293519774', 'english', 0, 2, '<p>EVN Finance has solemnly held the first anniversary to celebrate its 1 year establishment and officially come into operation from 01/9/2008 to 01/9/2009.</p>', '<p>EVN Finance has solemnly held the first anniversary to celebrate its 1 year establishment and officially come into operation from 01/9/2008 to 01/9/2009. <br />\r\nJoining finance and banking system in the context that the world economy experiencing serious crisis and Vietnamese economy being under great fluctuations, EVN Finance has encountered numerous difficulties and challenges. Nevertheless, with clear development orientation; great enthusiasm and strong determination of the leaders and staffs as well as&nbsp; the vital support of relating authorities departments and ministries and the strong cooperation and enthusiastic assistance of partners and customers; ENV Finance has considerably made further step to the expected target in the process of laying down the foundation and prestige&nbsp; within electricity sector and on Vietnamese financial market.&nbsp; <br />\r\nRight from the early days, beside stabilizing and establishing standard system, EVN Finance has actively developed and implemented necessary measures to increase the liquidity capacity, capital accumulation; actively expanded relationship on inter-bank market, mobilized capital from organizations within and outside Electricity of Vietnam (EVN) to generate a stable capital source for timely use. Together with fund raising, EVN Finance has been provided a wide range of&nbsp; useful and creative financial products in fund management and cash flow management for EVN and its subsidiaries, by which timely assist financial management activities and increase the efficiency by maximizing profitability of assets at these organizations.<br />\r\nWith the target to become the focal point of fund management and arrangement for EVN and its subsidiaries, EVN Finance has provided credit to organization within the sector, timely disbursed to meet construction progress and project operation of companies such as National Power Transmission Corporation, Son La Hydropower Project Management Board, Uong Bi Thermal Power JSC, Thac Mo Hydropower JSC, etc.<br />\r\nMoreover, EVN Finance has established and expanded partnerships with domestic and foreign financial institutes to efficiently arrange fund for key national electricity projects such as Huoi Quang Hydropower Project and Ban Chat Hydropower Project. Besides, EVN Finance has gradually provided credit to economic institutes such as corporations, enterprises with strong financial capability and efficient performance within construction sector, manufacturing sector and service sector.<br />\r\nTo gradually become the modern financial investment institutes, EVN Finance has established and implemented investment activities efficiently from contributing investment policies, selecting efficient investment portfolio. The target customers of EVN Finance includes EVN and its subsidiaries. EVN Finance has conducted a research, concentrated on capital contribution, valuable papers and efficient projects investment within the sector; ensuring achieving high effectiveness in the long term as well as timely meets investment needs. <br />\r\nQuang Ninh Thermal Power JSC, Hai Phong Thermal Power JSC, Thac Ba Thermal Power JSC, which played important role in national electricity development plan, are chosen as investment portfolio of EVN Finance. On the basis of conducting research activities, in-depth analysis of market and industry, EVN Finance has gradually implemented investment activities in other economic sectors to lay the ground for expanding relationships with partners as well as improving liquidity capacity, flexibility in risk prevention activities and increasing revenue and profit in the long term.<br />\r\nBearing in mind that implementing flexible and efficient financial advisory services is important to expand international relationship, increase income from service fees in the total revenue of the Company, over the last year, EVN Finance has provided EVN and other partners many services such as corporate financial advisory, financial management, bond issuing consultancy and other advisory services such as CDM &ndash; Clean Development Mechanism and investment consultancy. CDM advisory services have opportunity to develop when EVN Finance is being approved as a focal point to provide this service to EVN. Investment consultancy services create valuable opportunities for investors to invest in electricity sector.<br />\r\nTo become professional and modern investment financial institutes, EVN Finance concentrates on implementing credit and investment activities on the ground of providing wholesale financial products and services, identifying business development on the principle of secured and efficient accumulation in the long term as well as ensuring sustainability factor. EVN Finance concentrates on maintaining and developing international relationship together with creating cooperation opportunities, increasing the quantity and quality of customers, ensuring providing full package of useful and modern products, developing partners network by the professionalism and reputation which has been built in EVN Finance business culture.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Important milestones<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Decree of the Prime Minister No 507/TTg-DMDN dated 25 April 2007 on approving the establishment of EVN Finance Joint Stock Company.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The first shareholders&rsquo; committee of EVN Finance Joint Stock Company on 29 May 2008<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Establishment and operation certificate No 187/GP-NHNN issued by the State Bank of Vietnam on 07 July 2008<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business Registration Certificate No 0103025629 issued by Hanoi Department of Investment and Planning on 08 July 2008<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Officially come into operation on 01/9/2008<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Opening ceremony on 01 September 2008</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Business results<br />\r\n&nbsp;(By 30/06/2009)<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Registered capital: 2,500 billion VND<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Total asset: 8,641 billion VND (increase 188% compared to the end of 2008)<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outstanding capital mobilization: 5.418 billion VND<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outstanding credit: 1,428 billion VND<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outstanding investment: 3,016 billion VND</p>\r\n<p>Partners<br />\r\nFinancial institutes. Establishing relationship with 4 large commercial state banks including: Joint stock Commercial Bank for Foreign Trade of Vietnam (VCB), Vietnam Bank for Industry and Trade (Vietinbank),&nbsp; Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development of Vietnam (Agribank), Bank for Investment and Development of Vietnam (BIDV).<br />\r\nFinancial companies. PVFC, the Vietnam National Coal - Mineral Industries Group, Vinashin Finance, Rubber Finance Company; and over 40 domestic and foreign companies such as domestic commercial joint stock bank, foreign bank (ANZ, ADB), etc.<br />\r\nCorporates within Vietnam Electricity (EVN). Pha Lai Thermal Power JSC, Thac Ba Hydropower JSC, Son La Hydropower Project Management Board, Uong Bi Thermal Power company, Quang Ninh Thermal Power JSC, Hai Phong Thermal Power JSC, Thac Mo Hydropower JSC, Hanoi Power Company, Power Company No.1, Power Company No.2, Vietnam Power Development JSC, The National Power Transmission Corporation, Hai Phong Power OMC, EVN Telecom, etc.<br />\r\nEconomic institutes. Vietnam Air Petrol Company - VINAPCO, Refrigeration Electrical Engineering Company - REE, Thang Long Energy Company, Huyndai Dong Anh Steel Tower Manufacturing Company, Vina Fuji, MECO, etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '', '(EVNFinance)', 1, 'unhide'),
(55, 'news-amp-events', 'evnfinance-news', 'evn-finance-has-successfully-laid-down-its-prestige-via-the-vnd-4-trillion-issuance-of-evn-corporate-bond', 'EVN Finance has successfully laid down its prestige via the VND 4 trillion issuance of EVN corporate Bond', 'admin', '1293519880', 'admin', '1293519880', 'english', 0, 2, '<p>With less than 1 year of establishment, EVN Finance had laid down its prestige and trustworthiness of a large financial institution in Vietnam via this land-sliding event of which successfully underwritten VND 4 trillion EVN Bond.</p>', '<p>Under the shadow of global financial crisis which has been threatening the world economy, investing in bond seems to be a right option which has been perceived as a &quot;safe heaven&quot; for investors. <br />\r\nMoreover, the issuance of bond has been widely accepted as a safe and efficient ''''raising capital'''' instrument for enterprises. Therefore, due to the foregoing reasons, The Electricity of Vietnam (EVN) has considered raising capital vial issuance of bond is a vital channel of funding for electricity projects in order to meet the demand of urgent capital need for serving efficiently the development of the whole national economy. During the first 06 months of 2009; EVN Finance Joint Stock Company (EVN Finance) has been appointed as the focal point for fund arrangement for EVN''''s projects and EVN''''s subsidiaries. By acting as the arranger and underwriter, EVN Finance had successfully conducted an issuance of EVN bonds with the total value of up to VND 4 trillion.</p>\r\n<p>With less than 1 year of establishment, EVN Finance had laid down its prestige and trustworthiness of a large financial institution in Vietnam via this land-sliding event of which successfully underwritten VND 4 trillion EVN Bond.</p>\r\n<p>The issuance had attracted considerable interest of investors as well as the focus of media, marking a mile stone in the history of development on the Vietnamese corporate bond market in many aspects.</p>\r\n<p>Firstly, this transaction is the largest ever seen in the total value of a single corporate bond issuance for EVN, which the total value successfully issued of up to VND 3.5 trillion (accounted for the only second portion).</p>\r\n<p>Secondly, it had applied a new standard for bond issuance technique with the participation of very ''''large name'''' such as ANZ (EVN Finance and ANZ were the joint-lead managers and joint-book runners for the deal), JSM (the legal consultant) and expertise from EVN Finance, whereas the procedure for conducting a bond issuance reached international standard.</p>\r\n<p>Thirdly, it generated great momentum for the positive movement of Vietnam corporate bond market which has been &quot;frozen&quot; for a long time due to the adverse effect of low interest rate and high inflation in the past years, signaling a fruitful development of Vietnam Corporate Bond Market in the time to come.</p>\r\n<p>Finally, EVN Finance has committed to be the focal point in order to produce liquidity for EVN Bond by establishing a playing field for investors via its bond trading activities and therefore design the safe and efficient perception of investors regarding EVN Bond. This is an essential factor promising the success of the next coming EVN bond issuance.</p>\r\n<p>By successfully conduct this transaction; EVN Finance has set up its prestige and image of a professional and modern financial institution, displaying its right orientation toward being an investment bank in the time to come. Therefore, financial services such as bond issuance consultation, bond issuance underwriter have been one of the most important financial products of EVN Finance in the near future.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '', 'EVNFinance', 1, 'unhide'),
(56, 'news-amp-events', 'evnfinance-news', 'evnfinance-and-denmark-embassy-signing-memorandum-of-understanding-in-cooperation-to-implement-clean-development-mechanism-cdm', 'EVNFinance and Denmark Embassy signing Memorandum of Understanding in cooperation to implement Clean Development Mechanism (CDM)', 'admin', '1293519953', 'admin', '1293519953', 'english', 0, 2, '<p>On 14 July 2009, at the headquarter of EVNFinance Joint Stock Company (EVNFinance), EVNFinance and Denmark Embassy have signed the Memorandum of Understanding implementing CDM for energy projects in Vietnam.</p>', '<p>On 14 July 2009, at the headquarter of EVNFinance Joint Stock Company (EVNFinance), EVNFinance and Denmark Embassy have signed the Memorandum of Understanding implementing CDM for energy projects in Vietnam.<br />\r\nDenmark has been known as a developed country with many clean energy projects. EVNFinance, being a focal point for CDM development of Electricity of Vietnam, has gradually proved to play a key role in applying CDM to energy projects of Electricity of Vietnam.<br />\r\nEVNFinance and Denmark Embassy have spent time to study and search for cooperation opportunities in CDM activities. The signing ceremony is an important event marking the development of cooperation progress to develop and apply CDM to energy projects of EVN and its subsidiaries. At the ceremony, EVNFinance and Denmark Embassy&nbsp; showed determination in implementing feasible project of EVN.<br />\r\nThe signing ceremony is an remarkable milestone for the cooperation between EVNFinance and Denmark Embassy which lay ground for the collaboration oriented towards greener and cleaner energy for sustainable development.<br />\r\nAfter the signing ceremony, on 15th July 2009, in Hanoi, EVN, EVNFinance and Denmark Embassy together hold the workshop on &ldquo;Clean Development Mechanism&nbsp; in energy area&rdquo;, determining to implement planned target for potential development.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '', 'EVNFinance', 1, 'unhide'),
(57, 'news-amp-events', 'evnfinance-news', 'evnfinance-and-scic-signing-the-comprehensive-cooperation-agreement', 'EVNFINANCE and SCIC signing the Comprehensive Cooperation Agreement', 'admin', '1293520072', 'admin', '1293520072', 'english', 0, 2, '<p>On 16th July 2009, State Capital Investment Corporation (SCIC) and EVNFinance Joint Stock Company (EVNFinance) signed the Comprehensive Cooperation Agreement. According to the agreement,</p>', '<p>On 16th July 2009, State Capital Investment Corporation (SCIC) and EVNFinance Joint Stock Company (EVNFinance) signed the Comprehensive Cooperation Agreement. According to the agreement, EVNFinance committed to efficiently manage the deposit of SCIC at EVNFinance; cooperate with SCIC in buying shares of new domestic and international energy projects with an aim to invest and exploit the projects; simultaneously committed to exchange information and investment opportunities, especially cooperation opportunities in power development area, laying the ground for improving effectiveness of both parties, contributing to the socio-economic development of the nation.<br />\r\nAfter 10 months in operation, EVNFinance has achieved encouraging results on many areas. The total asset by the end of July 2009 reached over 8.500 million VND; business activities complying to regulations and practices; international relationship being expanded by developing domestic and international customer network.</p>\r\n<p>The signing of the Comprehensive Cooperation Agreement between SCIC and EVNFinance showed the willingness to cooperate and establish long-term relationship in the principle of voluntariness, equality, mutual benefits and understanding.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '', 'EVNFinance', 1, 'unhide'),
(58, 'news-amp-events', 'evnfinance-news', 'the-governor-of-the-state-bank-of-vietnam-have-meeting-with-leaders-of-evnfinance', 'The Governor of the State Bank of Vietnam have meeting with leaders of EVNFinance', 'admin', '1293520237', 'admin', '1293520237', 'english', 0, 2, '<p>On 15th July 2009, at the headquarter of the State Bank of Vietnam, leaders of EVNFinance Joint Stock Company (Chairman of Board of Management and General Director of EVNFinance) had a meeting with the Governor of the State Bank of Vietnam (SBV), to report on the operating results of EVNFinance after nearly 01 year of establishment.</p>', '<p>On 15th July 2009, at the headquarter of the State Bank of Vietnam, leaders of EVNFinance Joint Stock Company (Chairman of Board of Management and General Director of EVNFinance) had a meeting with the Governor of the State Bank of Vietnam (SBV), to report on the operating results of EVNFinance after nearly 01 year of establishment. <br />\r\nAt the meeting, the governor of SBV highly appreciated the effort of EVNFinance in achieving remarkable results after nearly 01 year of operation despite of the economic downturn. The governor has directed EVNFinance to focus on formulating appropriate development strategy, oriented towards sustainable development; simultaneously establishing an institute on the principle of abiding regulations and transparency, efficiently operate risk management system laying the solid ground for Management Board to implement appropriate management policy. Besides, the governor also emphasized that the development of human resources is the core to sustainable development.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nLeaders of EVNFinance reported on some constraints and obstacles in operation, proposed some suggestions creating foundation for operation of EVNFinance to achieve efficiency in its effort to implement target serving electricity industry &ndash; the backbone industry of the nation. The governor acknowledged difficulties of EVNFinance and promised to create favorable conditions for credit organizations in general and EVNFinance in particular to have the best favorable conditions to make full use of their strength in operation for the development of the nation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '', '(EVNFinance, 17/7/2009)', 1, 'unhide'),
(59, 'news-amp-events', 'evnfinance-news', 'evnfinance-and-agribank-signing-the-contract-of-e-banking-service', 'EVNFINANCE and AGRIBANK Signing the Contract of E-banking Service', 'admin', '1293520325', 'admin', '1293525338', 'english', 0, 2, '<p>On 8th August 2009, at the headquarter of EVNFinance Joint Stock Company (EVNFinance), Bank for Agricultural and Rural Development of Vietnam (Agribank) and EVNFinance signed the contract of e-banking services. Leaders of Electricity of Vietnam (EVN) and partners of the two parties have participated and witnessed the Signing Ceremony.</p>', '<p>On 8th August 2009, at the headquarter of EVNFinance Joint Stock Company (EVNFinance), Bank for Agricultural and Rural Development of Vietnam (Agribank) and EVNFinance signed the contract of e-banking services. Leaders of Electricity of Vietnam (EVN) and partners of the two parties have participated and witnessed the Signing Ceremony.<br />\r\nE-banking service provided by credit organizations to EVNFinance has efficiently assist EVNFinance in the arrangement and management of capital for EVN and its subsidiaries nationwide. This is one of the products which use modern technology to manage capital by automatically transferring money daily from various accounts to central account, supporting the electricity companies in the controlling and monitoring of capital as well as achieving better financial results.</p>\r\n<p>EVNFinance is established with the purpose of becoming the focal point in arranging and managing capital for EVN. With professional staff and appropriate policy and strategy, with the support of modern technology, in line with international standards, EVNFinance has provided a variety of financial products catering for particular clients; actively expanded international relationships on many areas with financial institutes, domestic and international economic organizations.<br />\r\n&nbsp; <br />\r\nAgribank, with the largest total asset in Vietnam financial system, plays a key role in capital investment to develop rural and agricultural economy as well as other areas of Vietnamese economy. Agribank focuses on investing and applying new technology serving the management and development of modern banking service network nationwide.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nEVNFinance totally believe that e-banking service provided by Agribank will efficiently assist the activities of EVNFinance, providing useful financial products to clients; promoting the close relationship, bringing mutual benefits and development of the nation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '', '(EVNFinance, 10/8/2009)', 1, ''),
(52, 'news-amp-events', 'evnfinance-news', 'evnfinance-being-awarded-trusted-stock-brand-2009', 'EVNFinance being awarded â€œTrusted Stock Brand - 2009â€', 'admin', '1293519447', 'admin', '1293519447', 'english', 0, 2, '<p>156 prominent listed and non-listed enterprises on Vietnam Stock Exchange have been granted with &ldquo;Trusted Stock Brand&rdquo; award on 11 October in Hanoi.</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>156 prominent listed and non-listed enterprises on Vietnam Stock Exchange have been granted with &ldquo;Trusted Stock Brand&rdquo; award on 11 October in Hanoi.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This nationwide award has been held annually since 2008&nbsp; for prominent enterprises on Vietnam Stock Exchange. The awards include the following: &ldquo;Top 100 Listed Enterprises in Vietnam&rdquo;; &ldquo;Trusted Public Company&rdquo;; &ldquo;Trusted Intermediary Institute of the Stock Exchange&rdquo;; and &ldquo;Trusted Stock Deposit Bank&rdquo;. Criteria to base on includes: Credit rating; General assessment on Company&rsquo;s Financial Index&rdquo;; Market capitalization; Registered capital, Capital ownership; The stability of Market price and the Liquidity of stocks; Transparency and regulatory compliance capacity on stock market; The effect of Stock brand on Stock Exchange; The effect of Enterprise/Brand on Consumer market; Management capacity; Strategic vision; Investment and Development potential; Achievements in Social activities and Contributions to the public, ect.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>100 listed enterprises, 30 non-listed enterprises, 26 intermediary institutes and service assistance organizations have been selected to grant the prizes.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Mr. Hoang Van Ninh &ndash; General Director of EVN Finance has represented the company to receive the award &ldquo;Top 30 non-listed companies in Vietnam&rdquo;. EVN Finance, with the achievement of this privileged award, has marked initial step in its effort to become one of the modern and strong financial institutions which operates efficiently, professionally and securely according to standards and norms towards sustainable development.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '', 'EVNFinance', 1, 'unhide'),
(53, 'news-amp-events', 'evnfinance-news', 'evnfinance-and-standard-chartered-bank-vietnam-signing-a-memorandum-of-understanding-mou', 'EVNFinance and Standard Chartered Bank Vietnam signing a Memorandum of Understanding (MOU)', 'admin', '1293519622', 'admin', '1293519622', 'english', 0, 2, '<p>On 19th October, 2009, in London, representative of EVN Finance Joint Stock Company (EVNFinance) - General Director, Mr Hoang Van Ninh and Mr Ashok Sud, General Director of Standard Chartered Bank in Vietnam, Laos and Cambodia have signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) at the witness of the Deputy Prime Minister of The Socialist Republic of Vietnam - Mr. Hoang Trung Hai and senior officials from the two countries.</p>', '<p>On 19th October, 2009, in London, representative of EVN Finance Joint Stock Company (EVNFinance) - General Director, Mr Hoang Van Ninh and Mr Ashok Sud, General Director of Standard Chartered Bank in Vietnam, Laos and Cambodia have signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) at the witness of the Deputy Prime Minister of The Socialist Republic of Vietnam - Mr. Hoang Trung Hai and senior officials from the two countries.<br />\r\nAccording to the MOU, the two parties will co-operate in the areas bringing mutual benefits such as: project financing, interest rate risk management and foreign exchange on domestic and international market.</p>\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fund Raising. Standard Chartered Bank and EVN Finance will partner to raise funds for the EVN Finance&rsquo;s key clients in local and international capital markets, through various funding channels including syndicated loans, bonds, project finance and securitisation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Money market and Foreign Exchange products. Standard Chartered Bank and EVN Finance will co-operate in sales and purchases of foreign currencies on the inter-bank market. The two parties will implement fixed income trading for Government, Municipal and Corporate bonds as well as support the other party in funding as necessary and within its limit and capacity.</p>\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Financial Hedging Instruments (Derivatives Products). Standard Chartered Bank will support and coordinate with EVNFinance in providing advisory services to corporate clients of ENVFinance on high-yielded investment products and financial hedging products. The Bank also consults in the implementation of derivatives products to minimize risks of projects of EVNFinance and EVNFinance&rsquo;s clients.</p>\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cash management. Standard Chartered is willing to provide EVNFinance a comprehensive range of cash management products and solutions including cash collection, payment solution, report and reconciliation, account structuring and liquidity management.</p>\r\n<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Training. Standard Chartered Bank and EVNFinance agree to co-operate in finance and banking product-training programs, experience exchanging of the banking technology and new products.</p>\r\n<p>With the mission to establish a centralized and unified financial system for EVN and its members, EVNFinance is established to provide financial products and services serving the development of EVN and its members. EVNFinance has been the important partner for many banks in Vietnam, providing and arranging fund for many national electricity projects; managing fund and cash flow for ENV and its members; being a bridge between domestic and international investors in electricity projects; being under process of receiving the authorization to manage government and international fund for electricity projects in Vietnam. EVNFinance also provide a variety of financial services to customers outside EVN system including corporate and personal lending, guarantees, project financing, foreign exchange and other services.</p>\r\n<p>Standard Chartered Bank has over 150 years development history on some of the most dynamic markets in the world and been a leading bank in Asia, Africa and the Middle East. The corporation now has more than 1,600 branches and agents in over 70 nations. The Bank has operated in Vietnam sice 1904 with the first branch in Saigon. Standard Chartered Bank Vietnam now has two branches in Hanoi and Ho Chi Minh City.</p>\r\n<p>Standard Chartered Bank provides full range of wholesale banking products and services to corporates, financial institutes, state enterprises and import-export enterprises. Besides, the Bank also provides retail banking services to serve personal and SMEs customers.</p>\r\n<p>After the Signing Ceremonty, Mr. Ashok Sud &ndash; General Director of Standard Chartered Bank in Vietnam, Laos and Cambodia expressed &lsquo;We&rsquo;re pleased to sign this Memorandum of Understanding and looking forward for good cooperation with EVNFinance. We believe this relationship will open up many opportunites for both EVNFinance and Standard Chartered Bank&rsquo;<br />\r\nSharing the same opinion, Mr. Hoang Van Ninh, General Director of EVNFinance asserted &lsquo;The Memorandum of Understanding between Standard Chartered Bank and EVNFinance has marked a significant step in the mutual relationship&rsquo;, and assured that EVNFinance will closely cooperate with Standard Chartered Bank to implement the committements to bring benefits for the two parties&rsquo;.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '', '(TCÄL, 20/10/2009)', 1, 'unhide'),
