(363, 'news-amp-events', 'evnfinance-news', 'fund-arrangement-for-buon-don-hydropower-plant-project', 'FUND ARRANGEMENT FOR BUON ÄON HYDROPOWER PLANT PROJECT', 'ducnt', '1332561355', 'ducnt', '1332561355', 'english', 0, 1, '<p>Further confirming the role of capital arrangement and administration for Vietnam Electricity (EVN) as well as its member companies, EVN Finance Joint Stock Company (EVNFinance) has successfully consulted to arrange funding package of USD 64.2 million for Srepok 4A Hydropower plant project of Buon Don Hydropower Joint Stock Company.</p>', '<p>On 15 March, 2012, Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corporation (SMBC) and Buon Don Hydropower Joint Stock Company held a ceremony at Nikko hotel to celebrate the success of credit contract worth $64.2 million lending Srepok 4A Hydropower Plant Project with 14-year loan term. <br />\r\nThe loan is financed under the overseas united loan insurance program of Nippon Export and Investment Insurance (NEXI) and guaranteed by Vietnamese Government. SMBC is original lender, mandated lead arranger and administrative agent. EVNFinance is financial advisor to BDHC and is a representative of BDHC to work with relevant Vietnamese authorities.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\nBuon Don Hydropower Joint Stock Company was established in 2009 by the shareholders: Power Engineering Consulting Company No. 4, Ba Ria Thermal Power Joint Stock Company, Pha Lai Thermal Power Joint Stock Company and Power Engineering Consulting Company No. 1, with the first purpose of conducting Srepok 4A Hydropower Plant Project at Buon Don District, DakLak province. All these shareholders are daughter companies of Vietnam Electricity. <br />\r\nWith the capacity of 64 MW, the project is a part of Master Plan on National Power Development from 2011 to 2020 with vision to 2030 (known as Master Plan VII) approved by Vietnamese Prime Minister. Srepok 4A hydropower plant is expected to generate 308 million kWh per year when it is completed in 2013, directly contributing to the economic development of central highland region. <br />\r\nDuring negotiations with SMBC, BDHC was granted short term loan by EVNFinance and Saigon &ndash; Hanoi Commercial Joint Stock Bank (SHB) to ensure the progress of project implementation. <br />\r\nFacing with instability of domestic and international financial market, capital arrangement schedule had been somewhat affected. With huge endeavor and determination, all parties have reached consensus and signed the contract on past 27 February, 2012. The cooperation in this project will furthermore enhance good relation between two countries, Japan and Vietnam.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '', '', 1, 'unhide'),
